{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1006,"text":"We have historical records that allow us\nto know how the ancient Greeks dressed,"},{"time":6180,"text":"how they lived,"},{"time":7458,"text":"how they fought ..."},{"time":9004,"text":"but how did they think?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":11432,"text":"One natural idea is that the deepest\naspects of human thought --"},{"time":15896,"text":"our ability to imagine,"},{"time":17792,"text":"to be conscious,"},{"time":19213,"text":"to dream --"},{"time":20468,"text":"have always been the same."},{"time":22872,"text":"Another possibility"},{"time":24395,"text":"is that the social transformations\nthat have shaped our culture"},{"time":28142,"text":"may have also changed\nthe structural columns of human thought."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32911,"text":"We may all have different\nopinions about this."},{"time":35459,"text":"Actually, it's a long-standing\nphilosophical debate."},{"time":38644,"text":"But is this question\neven amenable to science?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":42834,"text":"Here I'd like to propose"},{"time":45364,"text":"that in the same way we can reconstruct\nhow the ancient Greek cities looked"},{"time":50160,"text":"just based on a few bricks,"},{"time":52572,"text":"that the writings of a culture\nare the archaeological records,"},{"time":56722,"text":"the fossils, of human thought."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59905,"text":"And in fact,"},{"time":61103,"text":"doing some form of psychological analysis"},{"time":63333,"text":"of some of the most ancient\nbooks of human culture,"},{"time":66901,"text":"Julian Jaynes came up in the '70s\nwith a very wild and radical hypothesis:"},{"time":72880,"text":"that only 3,000 years ago,"},{"time":75317,"text":"humans were what today\nwe would call schizophrenics."},{"time":81753,"text":"And he made this claim"},{"time":83285,"text":"based on the fact that the first\nhumans described in these books"},{"time":86610,"text":"behaved consistently,"},{"time":88538,"text":"in different traditions\nand in different places of the world,"},{"time":91578,"text":"as if they were hearing and obeying voices"},{"time":95134,"text":"that they perceived\nas coming from the Gods,"},{"time":98198,"text":"or from the muses ..."},{"time":100063,"text":"what today we would call hallucinations."},{"time":103888,"text":"And only then, as time went on,"},{"time":106538,"text":"they began to recognize\nthat they were the creators,"},{"time":110213,"text":"the owners of these inner voices."},{"time":113316,"text":"And with this, they gained introspection:"},{"time":116055,"text":"the ability to think\nabout their own thoughts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":119785,"text":"So Jaynes's theory is that consciousness,"},{"time":123206,"text":"at least in the way we perceive it today,"},{"time":126396,"text":"where we feel that we are the pilots\nof our own existence --"},{"time":129960,"text":"is a quite recent cultural development."},{"time":133456,"text":"And this theory is quite spectacular,"},{"time":135266,"text":"but it has an obvious problem"},{"time":136723,"text":"which is that it's built on just a few\nand very specific examples."},{"time":141085,"text":"So the question is whether the theory"},{"time":142872,"text":"that introspection built up in human\nhistory only about 3,000 years ago"},{"time":147647,"text":"can be examined in a quantitative\nand objective manner."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151543,"text":"And the problem of how\nto go about this is quite obvious."},{"time":155130,"text":"It's not like Plato woke up one day\nand then he wrote,"},{"time":158614,"text":"\"Hello, I'm Plato,"},{"time":160297,"text":"and as of today, I have\na fully introspective consciousness.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":163210,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":165527,"text":"And this tells us actually\nwhat is the essence of the problem."},{"time":169467,"text":"We need to find the emergence\nof a concept that's never said."},{"time":174434,"text":"The word introspection\ndoes not appear a single time"},{"time":178768,"text":"in the books we want to analyze."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181728,"text":"So our way to solve this\nis to build the space of words."},{"time":186571,"text":"This is a huge space\nthat contains all words"},{"time":189882,"text":"in such a way that the distance\nbetween any two of them"},{"time":192708,"text":"is indicative of how\nclosely related they are."},{"time":196460,"text":"So for instance,"},{"time":197635,"text":"you want the words \"dog\" and \"cat\"\nto be very close together,"},{"time":200556,"text":"but the words \"grapefruit\" and \"logarithm\"\nto be very far away."},{"time":204809,"text":"And this has to be true\nfor any two words within the space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209626,"text":"And there are different ways\nthat we can construct the space of words."},{"time":212991,"text":"One is just asking the experts,"},{"time":214658,"text":"a bit like we do with dictionaries."},{"time":216896,"text":"Another possibility"},{"time":218348,"text":"is following the simple assumption\nthat when two words are related,"},{"time":222087,"text":"they tend to appear in the same sentences,"},{"time":224460,"text":"in the same paragraphs,"},{"time":225937,"text":"in the same documents,"},{"time":227731,"text":"more often than would be expected\njust by pure chance."},{"time":232231,"text":"And this simple hypothesis,"},{"time":234305,"text":"this simple method,"},{"time":235635,"text":"with some computational tricks"},{"time":237266,"text":"that have to do with the fact"},{"time":238679,"text":"that this is a very complex\nand high-dimensional space,"},{"time":241767,"text":"turns out to be quite effective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244155,"text":"And just to give you a flavor\nof how well this works,"},{"time":246981,"text":"this is the result we get when\nwe analyze this for some familiar words."},{"time":251607,"text":"And you can see first"},{"time":252816,"text":"that words automatically organize\ninto semantic neighborhoods."},{"time":256118,"text":"So you get the fruits, the body parts,"},{"time":258359,"text":"the computer parts,\nthe scientific terms and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261119,"text":"The algorithm also identifies\nthat we organize concepts in a hierarchy."},{"time":265852,"text":"So for instance,"},{"time":267027,"text":"you can see that the scientific terms\nbreak down into two subcategories"},{"time":270648,"text":"of the astronomic and the physics terms."},{"time":273338,"text":"And then there are very fine things."},{"time":275608,"text":"For instance, the word astronomy,"},{"time":277537,"text":"which seems a bit bizarre where it is,"},{"time":279376,"text":"is actually exactly where it should be,"},{"time":281448,"text":"between what it is,"},{"time":283067,"text":"an actual science,"},{"time":284361,"text":"and between what it describes,"},{"time":285921,"text":"the astronomical terms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288182,"text":"And we could go on and on with this."},{"time":290097,"text":"Actually, if you stare\nat this for a while,"},{"time":292181,"text":"and you just build random trajectories,"},{"time":294063,"text":"you will see that it actually feels\na bit like doing poetry."},{"time":298018,"text":"And this is because, in a way,"},{"time":299924,"text":"walking in this space\nis like walking in the mind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":304027,"text":"And the last thing"},{"time":305668,"text":"is that this algorithm also identifies\nwhat are our intuitions,"},{"time":309732,"text":"of which words should lead\nin the neighborhood of introspection."},{"time":313652,"text":"So for instance,"},{"time":314899,"text":"words such as \"self,\" \"guilt,\"\n\"reason,\" \"emotion,\""},{"time":318902,"text":"are very close to \"introspection,\""},{"time":320815,"text":"but other words,"},{"time":321990,"text":"such as \"red,\" \"football,\"\n\"candle,\" \"banana,\""},{"time":324181,"text":"are just very far away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326054,"text":"And so once we've built the space,"},{"time":328840,"text":"the question of the history\nof introspection,"},{"time":331690,"text":"or of the history of any concept"},{"time":334047,"text":"which before could seem abstract\nand somehow vague,"},{"time":338850,"text":"becomes concrete --"},{"time":340478,"text":"becomes amenable to quantitative science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344216,"text":"All that we have to do is take the books,"},{"time":347002,"text":"we digitize them,"},{"time":348407,"text":"and we take this stream\nof words as a trajectory"},{"time":351240,"text":"and project them into the space,"},{"time":353233,"text":"and then we ask whether this trajectory\nspends significant time"},{"time":357011,"text":"circling closely to the concept\nof introspection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360760,"text":"And with this,"},{"time":361980,"text":"we could analyze\nthe history of introspection"},{"time":364116,"text":"in the ancient Greek tradition,"},{"time":366061,"text":"for which we have the best\navailable written record."},{"time":369631,"text":"So what we did is we took all the books --"},{"time":371910,"text":"we just ordered them by time --"},{"time":374218,"text":"for each book we take the words"},{"time":375994,"text":"and we project them to the space,"},{"time":377979,"text":"and then we ask for each word\nhow close it is to introspection,"},{"time":381035,"text":"and we just average that."},{"time":382590,"text":"And then we ask whether,\nas time goes on and on,"},{"time":385812,"text":"these books get closer,\nand closer and closer"},{"time":389088,"text":"to the concept of introspection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390866,"text":"And this is exactly what happens\nin the ancient Greek tradition."},{"time":395698,"text":"So you can see that for the oldest books\nin the Homeric tradition,"},{"time":398849,"text":"there is a small increase with books\ngetting closer to introspection."},{"time":402285,"text":"But about four centuries before Christ,"},{"time":404515,"text":"this starts ramping up very rapidly\nto an almost five-fold increase"},{"time":409247,"text":"of books getting closer,\nand closer and closer"},{"time":411771,"text":"to the concept of introspection."},{"time":414159,"text":"And one of the nice things about this"},{"time":416607,"text":"is that now we can ask"},{"time":417829,"text":"whether this is also true\nin a different, independent tradition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":422962,"text":"So we just ran this same analysis\non the Judeo-Christian tradition,"},{"time":426162,"text":"and we got virtually the same pattern."},{"time":429548,"text":"Again, you see a small increase\nfor the oldest books in the Old Testament,"},{"time":434207,"text":"and then it increases much more rapidly"},{"time":436145,"text":"in the new books of the New Testament."},{"time":438008,"text":"And then we get the peak of introspection"},{"time":440064,"text":"in \"The Confessions of Saint Augustine,\""},{"time":442215,"text":"about four centuries after Christ."},{"time":444897,"text":"And this was very important,"},{"time":446865,"text":"because Saint Augustine\nhad been recognized by scholars,"},{"time":450262,"text":"philologists, historians,"},{"time":452458,"text":"as one of the founders of introspection."},{"time":455060,"text":"Actually, some believe him to be\nthe father of modern psychology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459012,"text":"So our algorithm,"},{"time":460875,"text":"which has the virtue\nof being quantitative,"},{"time":463741,"text":"of being objective,"},{"time":465028,"text":"and of course of being extremely fast --"},{"time":467068,"text":"it just runs in a fraction of a second --"},{"time":469489,"text":"can capture some of the most\nimportant conclusions"},{"time":473016,"text":"of this long tradition of investigation."},{"time":476317,"text":"And this is in a way\none of the beauties of science,"},{"time":479992,"text":"which is that now this idea\ncan be translated"},{"time":483492,"text":"and generalized to a whole lot\nof different domains."}]},{"cues":[{"time":486769,"text":"So in the same way that we asked\nabout the past of human consciousness,"},{"time":491560,"text":"maybe the most challenging question\nwe can pose to ourselves"},{"time":494990,"text":"is whether this can tell us something\nabout the future of our own consciousness."},{"time":499550,"text":"To put it more precisely,"},{"time":501044,"text":"whether the words we say today"},{"time":503484,"text":"can tell us something\nof where our minds will be in a few days,"},{"time":508705,"text":"in a few months"},{"time":509880,"text":"or a few years from now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511597,"text":"And in the same way many of us\nare now wearing sensors"},{"time":514641,"text":"that detect our heart rate,"},{"time":516451,"text":"our respiration,"},{"time":517744,"text":"our genes,"},{"time":519435,"text":"on the hopes that this may\nhelp us prevent diseases,"},{"time":523110,"text":"we can ask whether monitoring\nand analyzing the words we speak,"},{"time":526655,"text":"we tweet, we email, we write,"},{"time":529362,"text":"can tell us ahead of time whether\nsomething may go wrong with our minds."},{"time":535087,"text":"And with Guillermo Cecchi,"},{"time":536645,"text":"who has been my brother in this adventure,"},{"time":539670,"text":"we took on this task."},{"time":542228,"text":"And we did so by analyzing\nthe recorded speech of 34 young people"},{"time":547784,"text":"who were at a high risk\nof developing schizophrenia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":551434,"text":"And so what we did is,\nwe measured speech at day one,"},{"time":554339,"text":"and then we asked whether the properties\nof the speech could predict,"},{"time":557605,"text":"within a window of almost three years,"},{"time":560125,"text":"the future development of psychosis."},{"time":563427,"text":"But despite our hopes,"},{"time":565817,"text":"we got failure after failure."},{"time":569793,"text":"There was just not enough\ninformation in semantics"},{"time":573699,"text":"to predict the future\norganization of the mind."},{"time":576516,"text":"It was good enough"},{"time":578349,"text":"to distinguish between a group\nof schizophrenics and a control group,"},{"time":582548,"text":"a bit like we had done\nfor the ancient texts,"},{"time":585284,"text":"but not to predict the future\nonset of psychosis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":589164,"text":"But then we realized"},{"time":590894,"text":"that maybe the most important thing\nwas not so much what they were saying,"},{"time":595006,"text":"but how they were saying it."},{"time":597679,"text":"More specifically,"},{"time":598923,"text":"it was not in which semantic\nneighborhoods the words were,"},{"time":601774,"text":"but how far and fast they jumped"},{"time":604398,"text":"from one semantic neighborhood\nto the other one."},{"time":607247,"text":"And so we came up with this measure,"},{"time":609002,"text":"which we termed semantic coherence,"},{"time":611415,"text":"which essentially measures the persistence\nof speech within one semantic topic,"},{"time":616243,"text":"within one semantic category."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619294,"text":"And it turned out to be\nthat for this group of 34 people,"},{"time":623365,"text":"the algorithm based on semantic\ncoherence could predict,"},{"time":627048,"text":"with 100 percent accuracy,"},{"time":629572,"text":"who developed psychosis and who will not."},{"time":632976,"text":"And this was something\nthat could not be achieved --"},{"time":635937,"text":"not even close --"},{"time":637469,"text":"with all the other\nexisting clinical measures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":642525,"text":"And I remember vividly,\nwhile I was working on this,"},{"time":646128,"text":"I was sitting at my computer"},{"time":648469,"text":"and I saw a bunch of tweets by Polo --"},{"time":651128,"text":"Polo had been my first student\nback in Buenos Aires,"},{"time":654319,"text":"and at the time\nhe was living in New York."},{"time":656413,"text":"And there was something in this tweets --"},{"time":658525,"text":"I could not tell exactly what\nbecause nothing was said explicitly --"},{"time":662050,"text":"but I got this strong hunch,"},{"time":664095,"text":"this strong intuition,\nthat something was going wrong."},{"time":668347,"text":"So I picked up the phone,\nand I called Polo,"},{"time":671094,"text":"and in fact he was not feeling well."},{"time":673362,"text":"And this simple fact,"},{"time":675323,"text":"that reading in between the lines,"},{"time":677838,"text":"I could sense,\nthrough words, his feelings,"},{"time":682124,"text":"was a simple, but very\neffective way to help."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685987,"text":"What I tell you today"},{"time":687649,"text":"is that we're getting\nclose to understanding"},{"time":690181,"text":"how we can convert this intuition\nthat we all have,"},{"time":694491,"text":"that we all share,"},{"time":695880,"text":"into an algorithm."},{"time":698102,"text":"And in doing so,"},{"time":699587,"text":"we may be seeing in the future\na very different form of mental health,"},{"time":704261,"text":"based on objective, quantitative\nand automated analysis"},{"time":709906,"text":"of the words we write,"},{"time":711639,"text":"of the words we say."}]},{"cues":[{"time":713200,"text":"Gracias."}]},{"cues":[{"time":714375,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}